analysis: The documents in this cluster all pertain to the establishment, modification, or authorization of awards, seals, and flags by the President of the United States. These honors are intended to recognize significant contributions and service in various fields, including government service, military service, export expansion, and wartime efforts. The documents also establish boards and procedures for selecting recipients and defining the criteria for these honors.
title: Establishment and Modification of Presidential Awards, Seals, and Flags
